column28: The main issue is that while I noticed that you needed to enter the OTE for each quarter, I doubt many other people will notice this. Normal individual employees do not think in terms of 'quarters' (this is more a 'business' or 'government' thing). Individuals will think in terms of pay packets. Because of this, I think putting in exact dates is good. But I also think people should be able to choose from a drop-down list what bracket they'd like to put an amount in for. (e.g. I get paid fortnightly, so I want to be able to choose the overall period I'm checking my super for, select 'fortnightly', then enter the amount I earn fortnightly.) This way it focuses on what's easiest for me, not what makes sense to the government organisation.
